                            <comment id="13127733" author="madhuvaidya" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 17:56:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently it is calculated based on creation time (that is part of the file name). But for low traffic RS, there could be a case where a file is created and has no edits for a really long time. Then newer edits will be written to this HLog and once it is rolled over to .oldlogs, it will be deleted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127736" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 17:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
